123
00:07:07,045 --> 00:07:11,145
I see. He ran and perspired,

124
00:07:11,145 --> 00:07:13,345
so that he could distract everyone from the fact

125
00:07:13,345 --> 00:07:15,045
that he was perspiring from panic.

126
00:07:15,045 --> 00:07:18,417
Wait a sec. Even if he were the culprit,

127
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:22,421
he couldn't have gone to all three festivals that were held?

128
00:07:22,645 --> 00:07:24,423
If so, there has to be somebody

129
00:07:24,423 --> 00:07:27,745
other than him who is Rooster Man,

130
00:07:28,945 --> 00:07:30,429
but the knapsack had things

131
00:07:30,645 --> 00:07:33,545
that were stolen from all three festivals inside it.

132
00:07:33,545 --> 00:07:37,145
Besides, what does monkey and the number 9 mean?

133
00:07:37,145 --> 00:07:39,545
What on earth does it mean?

134
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:43,445
What's the matter, Conan? Why that dreadfully serious look?

135
00:07:43,445 --> 00:07:47,445
Yep. I was just wondering what monkey and the number 9 mean.

136
00:07:47,445 --> 00:07:49,845
Monkey and 9 (Saru and Kyu).

137
00:07:49,845 --> 00:07:52,451
Dad, what brings you here?

138
00:07:52,451 --> 00:07:54,145
I heard that Rooster Man appeared again

139
00:07:54,145 --> 00:07:56,745
and that you guys came to,

140
00:07:56,745 --> 00:07:59,445
so I got worried and came to pick you up.

141
00:07:59,445 --> 00:08:01,445
It was big news on TV

142
00:08:01,445 --> 00:08:02,745
that the guy who was stabbed

143
00:08:02,745 --> 00:08:06,465
left a mysterious message of monkey and the number 9 behind.

144
00:08:07,645 --> 00:08:10,745
What the word "kyu" brings to mind for me is...

145
00:08:10,745 --> 00:08:14,473
kyukancho (myna bird), kyukyusha (ambulance),

146
00:08:14,473 --> 00:08:18,145
takkyu (table tennis) or yakyu (baseball)!

147
00:08:18,145 --> 00:08:23,045
But, I don't recall any baseball ground with the word Saru in it.

148
00:08:23,045 --> 00:08:27,745
Talking of baseball grounds, the Koshien Kyujo,

149
00:08:27,745 --> 00:08:30,245
what is it called Koshien (monkey-child-park)?

150
00:08:30,245 --> 00:08:33,145
Was there a place called Koshien in that area?

151
00:08:33,145 --> 00:08:36,045
Yes, there is! Like Koshien Station.

152
00:08:36,045 --> 00:08:37,245
No.

153
00:08:37,245 --> 00:08:38,945
The name of the place was named what it is now,

154
00:08:38,945 --> 00:08:41,145
after the Koshien Baseball Park was made there.

155
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:44,045
And the year the Koshien Baseball Park was built is...

156
00:08:45,245 --> 00:08:48,245
What about the year it was built?

157
00:08:48,245 --> 00:08:50,845
I see. So, that's what it was...

158
00:08:50,845 --> 00:08:53,845
The victim knew the culprit.

159
00:08:53,845 --> 00:08:55,945
That's why he referred to the 9th monkey.

160
00:08:56,945 --> 00:08:59,145
Okay, let's go home!

161
00:09:00,145 --> 00:09:02,521
Oh, I forgot!

162
00:09:02,521 --> 00:09:05,845
I've got to go pick up my laundry at the cleaners before I go home.

163
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:08,845
Dad, will you go on ahead and take Conan and Sonoko home!

164
00:09:09,845 --> 00:09:11,945
You can go pick it up tomorrow!

165
00:09:11,945 --> 00:09:15,645
You're attending a friend's wedding tomorrow, aren't you, Dad?

166
00:09:34,945 --> 00:09:38,557
