195
00:11:11,145 --> 00:11:14,145
and number 9 that the university student who was stabbed remarked of?

196
00:11:14,145 --> 00:11:16,655
Yep. The man who was stabbed

197
00:11:16,845 --> 00:11:19,445
knew the man who stabbed him!

198
00:11:19,445 --> 00:11:22,661
That's why he said, "He's not a rooster, but a monkey",

199
00:11:22,661 --> 00:11:24,663
and showed nine of his fingers.

200
00:11:24,663 --> 00:11:26,245
Then, it's that man

201
00:11:26,245 --> 00:11:27,945
that has a monkey looking face called Tatsuo Hino, right?

202
00:11:27,945 --> 00:11:29,245
If they knew each other,

203
00:11:29,245 --> 00:11:30,345
he would know the face of the one who stabbed him, wouldn't he?

204
00:11:30,345 --> 00:11:33,645
But, he has nothing to do with the number 9, does he?

205
00:11:33,645 --> 00:11:36,675
Then, is it the man called Hisami Sarukawa?

206
00:11:36,675 --> 00:11:38,945
His nickname seems to be Kyu-chan too.

207
00:11:38,945 --> 00:11:41,445
Besides if he was close enough to know the nickname of the culprit.

208
00:11:41,445 --> 00:11:42,681
I'm sure he would've mentioned the nickname

209
00:11:42,681 --> 00:11:45,745
and directly say that the culprit is Sarukawa.

210
00:11:45,745 --> 00:11:49,945
But the only one left is Shinji Mizunoe then?

211
00:11:49,945 --> 00:11:52,691
What's monkey and number 9 about him?

212
00:11:52,691 --> 00:11:55,545
The character "tori" that is used for Tori no Ichi refers to the "tori"

213
00:11:55,545 --> 00:11:57,445
as know in the twelve horary signs of the lunar calendar, right?

214
00:11:57,445 --> 00:11:58,697
So what about the monkey character?

215
00:11:58,697 --> 00:12:01,145
Well...

216
00:12:01,145 --> 00:12:03,645
The character "shin" is the character

217
00:12:03,645 --> 00:12:05,845
used in the name of Shinji Mizunoe.

